channel.title: CVE Feed for Jenkins project -- Jenkins GitHub Authentication Plugin
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Jenkins project -- Jenkins GitHub Authentication Plugin

item.title: CVE-2019-1003019|2024-08-05T03:00:19.434Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20github%20authentication%20plugin
item.description: An session fixation vulnerability exists in Jenkins GitHub Authentication Plugin 0.29 and earlier in GithubSecurityRealm.java that allows unauthorized attackers to impersonate another user if they can control the pre-authentication session.

item.title: CVE-2019-1003018|2024-08-05T03:00:19.283Z -- jenkins%20project -- jenkins%20github%20authentication%20plugin
item.description: An exposure of sensitive information vulnerability exists in Jenkins GitHub Authentication Plugin 0.29 and earlier in GithubSecurityRealm/config.jelly that allows attackers able to view a Jenkins administrator's web browser output, or control the browser (e.g. malicious extension) to retrieve the configured client secret.
